Whisk 2 tablespoons oil, vinegar and thyme in small bowl to blend. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and shallots; saut√© until beginning to brown, about 3 minutes. Cover skillet; cook until mushrooms are tender, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes. Uncover; simmer until any juices evaporate. Mix 2 tablespoons dressing and chives into mushrooms. Season with salt and pepper. Toss greens with remaining dressing in large bowl. Top with mushrooms.